==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin ''[[turpitudo]]'', from ''[[turpis]]'' "foul, base"

===Noun===
'''turpitude'''

# [[inherent|Inherent]] [[baseness]] or [[depravity]]; [[corruptness]] and [[evilness]].
#: ''The delinquent juvenile was guilty of moral '''turpitude'''.''
# An act [[evident]] of such a depravity.

